vulnerability.name: CVE-2007-6059
vulnerability.description: ** DISPUTED ** Javamail does not properly handle a series of invalid login attempts in which the same e-mail address is entered as username and password, and the domain portion of this address yields a Java UnknownHostException error, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (connection pool exhaustion) via a large number of requests, resulting in a SQLNestedException. NOTE: Sun disputes this issue, stating "The report makes references to source code and files that do not exist in the mentioned products."

vulnerability.name: CVE-2007-0156
vulnerability.description: M-Core stores the database under the web document root, which allows remote attackers to obtain sensitive information via a direct request to db/uyelik.mdb.

vulnerability.name: CVE-2012-0213
vulnerability.description: The UnhandledDataStructure function in hwpf/model/UnhandledDataStructure.java in Apache POI 3.8 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (OutOfMemoryError exception and possibly JVM destabilization) via a crafted length value in a Channel Definition Format (CDF) or Compound File Binary Format (CFBF) document.
